## Backward Euler


In Backward Euler we replace the forward-difference with a backward-difference,
that is
$$
{u_k - u_{k-1} \over h} - a(t_k) u_k = f(u_k)
$$
This leads to the system:
$$
\begin{bmatrix}
ðž_1^âŠ¤ \\
D_h -  I_n^{\rm b}  A_n
\end{bmatrix} ð®^{\rm b} = \underbrace{ \begin{bmatrix}
1 \\
-1/h & 1/h -a(t_2)\\
& \ddots & \ddots \\
&& -1/h & 1/h-a(t_n)
\end{bmatrix}}_L ð®^{\rm b} = \begin{bmatrix} c \\ I_n^{\rm b} ðŸ \end{bmatrix}
$$
Again this is a bidiagonal forward-substitution:
$$
\begin{align*}
u_1 &= c \\
(1 - h a(t_{k+1})) u_{k+1} &= u_k + h f(t_{k+1})
\end{align*}
$$
That is,
$$
u_{k+1} = (1 - h a(t_{k+1}))^{-1}(u_k + h f(t_{k+1}))
$$




